    rationale: "The summation gallop forms because tachycardia shortens diastole enough to merge S3 and S4. Slowing the heart rate with a beta-blocker lengthens diastole, allowing the two sounds to separate again. Atrial fibrillation would eliminate S4 (no atrial contraction) but would not restore the separation. Diuretics reduce preload and may diminish S3 intensity but do not directly address the rate-dependent merging. Positioning enhances auscultation but does not change the underlying mechanism.",
