    prompt: "A 65-year-old man with a known harsh systolic murmur at the right second intercostal space loses consciousness while climbing stairs. He regains consciousness within 30 seconds. What is the most dangerous mechanism responsible for this event, and why does it differ from a vasovagal episode?",
