    rationale: "The AV node introduces a physiologic delay (approximately 120\u2013200 ms, reflected as the PR interval) that allows atrial contraction to complete before ventricular systole begins. This 'atrial kick' contributes approximately 15\u201330% of ventricular filling (more in patients with diastolic dysfunction). Without this delay, the atria and ventricles would contract simultaneously, reducing ventricular end-diastolic volume and stroke volume. While the AV node does limit ventricular rate during atrial fibrillation, this is a secondary function, not the primary physiologic purpose of the delay.",
