    rationale: "In complete heart block, atria and ventricles beat independently. The atria no longer contract in coordination with ventricular diastole, eliminating the atrial kick (the active component of ventricular filling). This reduces end-diastolic volume and stroke volume. While passive filling continues, the loss of the atrial contribution (15\u201330% of filling, more in diastolic dysfunction) significantly reduces cardiac output. The ventricular escape rhythm restores a heartbeat but does not restore AV synchrony \u2014 it is typically slow (30\u201340 bpm) and further reduces cardiac output.",
